|2l 84 Col Oil A Gas vtc. 9 9 9 4\n554 24 Columbia Pic 38 364 38+5\nI 64 34 Coml A S war 34 34 34\u2014 4\n274 15 Cons Aircraft.... 22 22 22\n84 34 Cons Cooper Ml.. 4 4 4\n11364 904 Cons Gas Balt 3.6< 113 11-4 U 3 +24\nI 194 114 Com Water 6%b. 124 124 124- 4\n[l3 74 Cons Retail St 1.. 74 74 74- 4\n744 32 Cosden Oil 38 364+ 4\nI 74 54 Creole Petrol 6 6 6 4\nI 654 35 Cumb Pipe 4a.... 35 35 35\n514 34 Cuneo Press 374 374 374+ 4\nI 44 14 Cur Wrixht war.. 14 14 14\n\u2014D\u2014\n-1624 85 Deere ACo new.. 914 904 914+ 14\n&4 24 'DeForest Rad.... 34 i 4 o 4\u2014 4\nI 84 64 De Havil Air new 74 74 74+ 4\n94 5 Det Aircraft 54 54 54\ni 564 31 Dresser Mte A3U .94 394 394+ 4\nBargains Seen in Market\nFor Investment Holders\nBy LEWIS HANEY\nDirector of New York University Bureau\nof Business Research and Former\nEconomist of Federal Trade\nCommission\nLass week\u2019s stocks dipped and\nrallied, closing a point or two\nhigher than at the end of the pre\nceding week. The market, hov'-\never, was very irregular, and 00-h\nrails and bonds lost ground.\nOnly 15,000,000 shares changed\nhands all week, which compared\nwith 26,0000,000 the week before\nand nearly 20,000,000 a year ago.\nClearly the temporary equilibrium\nwas established. A \u201cresistance\nlevel\u201d was reached. Selling dried\nup, but buying for an advance\nwould not take hold.\nThere is no evidence that a\nsustained advance is in the mak\ning. The market is merely over\nsold for the time being, and is\npausing to await more definite in\ndications concerning the business\noutlook, as there is nothing op\ntimistic in that quarter (except\ntalk). We may expect further\nweakness in due course. The small\ntrader has little chance in the\nmarket. Certainly he should take\nsmall profits (or losses) quickly.\nI am inclined to think that stop\nloss orders should be placed at\nthe level of last Tuesday\u2019s close.\nTs there is to be another down\nswing it will probably be indi\ncated by a break through that\nlevel.\nI still advise holding sound\ndividend stocks, which show\nearnings to justify amply the\npresent price. In such cases, you\nmight as well forget what you\noriginally paid for them. If the\n-present price is not over 10 times\nprobable earnings this year, it\nimay be well to buy some more\nf n order to \u201caverage down\u201d your\ntost.\nThis applies particularly to the\nBound old-line industrials whicn\nWere not skyrocketed last year,\nBind to the high class rails, but\nbeware of the blue chips of 1929.\nutilities, and the stocks which\nlire now showing extremely high\ndividends and very low price earn-\nWig ratios. Also beware of com\ng*anies which are going to be com\npelled to do financing now (North\nAmerican, Warner Brothers and\nBethlehem Steel). New capita!\nIs going to cost them plenty and\nFour equity will be reduced.\n\u2022It is a good time to pick up\nbargains for investment holding,\nthough one should remember that\nthis is a real major bear market\nfcr.d not be in any hurry. But\non a scale down, or when things\niodk the darkest during the next\nrecession.\nlike especially such stocks _as\nAmerican Smelting. Allis Chai-\nJners, Union Tank. Continental\nCari. Drug Inc.. Mathieson Alkali\nAnd| Liggett and Myers.\nu T\u00bbvo factors now predominate\nin the market. One is pausing\nto await definite signs of any re\ncovery in the fall. The other is\nthe supply of undigested securities\nand the related credit situation.\nHuge collateral loans continue to\nshow that a great mass of.stocks\nand bonds are not really paid for.\nIt is not likely that this bear\nmarket will end until the col\nlateral loan situation has been\ngreatly liquidated, and until there\nis something more than talk\nabout \u201ceasy money\u201d and \u201cshort\nages in the making\u201d to indicate\nbusiness recovery.\nTaxation Examined\nAt Officials' Parley\nSALT LAKE CITY, July 1\n(I.N.S.).\u2014Taxation of national\nbanks will occupy the brief busi\nness session scheduled today for\nthe meeting of the national gov\nernors conference here, alter\nwhich the twenty odd chief ex\necutives will be given opportunity\nfor a plunge in the Great Salt\nLake and later taken on an in\nspection trip of the large copper\nmines in the Bingham district.\nGov. Clyde M. Reed, of Kansas,\nis scheduled to deliver the chief\naddress today on bank taxation.\nGovernor Hardman, of Georgia,\ninvited the conference to hold its\n1931 sessions in that State, and\nGovernor Young, of California,\nmade a bid for the 1932 con\nference.\n7 Mo. Bond Calls\nLowest Since 1924\nCorporation bonds and notes\ncalled for payment in advance of\nmaturity in July, 1930, total $44,-\n654,990, against $29,926,070 in\nJune and $56,030,850 in July.\n1929. Os the current total $40,-\n251,540 was called in entirety\nand $4,403,450 was called in part,\ngenerally to satisfy sinking fund\nrequirements.\nThe combined total of $235,990.-\n810 for the first seven months of\nthis year is the lowest since 1924\nand compares with $473,581,660\nfor the corresponding period of\n1929.\nCalif. Crude Oil\nOutput Shows Drop\nCalifornia crude oil output in\nthe week ended June 28 averaged\n599,900 barrels daily, a decrease\nof 4,100 from the previous week,\nCalifornia Oil World estimated\ntoday.\nFOREIGN BONDS\nFrench Government 4s 40\nFrench Government 5s 40\nFrench Premium 5b 52*4\nFrench of 192 S 39*4\nBelgium Premium fin 23%\n\u25a0HelS\u2019ian Restoration 5a 27\nBritish War Loan On 43*\nBritish Victory 4s 424\nItalian War Lean oa 43\nTHE WASHINGTON TIMES\n~-Pr\u00abv. 1930\u2014. N\u00bbm\u00bb and Net\nHigh Low Dividend Rata High Low 1:1S Cb'ga\n209 140 Duke Power 6a... 151 151 151 1\n7 24 Durant 24 24 24- 4\n17 j. 84 DuauesneGaa.... 94 94 94\u201c 4\n42 254 East Gas A F.... 31 30 30 -4\n44 184 East St P B 1.... .6 26 26 -1\n23 94 Eisler Elect 14.. 10 94 10-4\n1174 704 Elec BAS 6%b.. 814 <B4 80 4\n1094 1034 Elec B 4 8 of 1.. 165 1044 1044- 4\n94 924 El BAB 6 pr....*. 124 924 124- 4\n394 19 Elec Pwr Assn 1. 23