rd flats.\n12s and 15s, $1.90@2. South Carolina,\ngreen meats, standard 24s and 365,\n$2.75. Honey Dews: Three California\narrived; 1 reconsigned; 10 cars on track,\nincluding broken. Supplies moderate;\ndemand slow; market dull. California,\nstandard crates. 8s and 9s, $2.75; 12s,\n$2.25@2.50; jumbo 365, $4.25; standard\n36s and 455, $3.75. Honey Balls: One\nCalifornia arrived: 1 broken car on\ntrack. Supplies light; demand mod\nerate; market unsettled. California,\nstandard flats, 12s and 15s, mostly\n$1.75; standard 455, $5@5.50; pony 455,\nmostly $4.\nCarrots\u2014No arrivals; 6 cars on track\nincluding broken. Supplies moderate;\ndemand slow; market dull. California\nwestern lettuce crates, bunched, best,\n$2.75@3; poorer. $2@2.50.\nCelery\u2014Supplies moderate. California,\nfull crates, mostly $6; two-third crates,\n$5@5.50. New York, full crates, $5.75\n@6; one-half cratei, best, $3.50; poorer,\n$2.50@2.75.\nCorn\u2014Three Alabama, 1 North Caro\nlina arrived; 4 cars on track, including\nbroken. North Carolina express receipts\nlight. Nearby receipts light. Supplies\nmoderate; demand good; market about\nsteady. Alabama, crates, $2@2.25\nNdrth Carolina, refrigerator car. crates,\nmostly $2. Nearby, per doz.. 30 35c.\nCucumbers\u2014Supplies liberal. South\nern, bu. hampers, fancy, 25@50c, few\nhigher; choice. 25@50c. Nearby, Vs-bu.\nhampers, 50@65c.\nEggplants \u2014No car-lot arrivals; no\ncars on track. Virginia. Norfolk and\nHampton bota receipts light. Supplies\nlight; demand moderate' market steady.\nVirginia, Norfolk and Hampton, one\nhalf crates, $2.75@3.\nHuckleberries \u2014Sn p p I les moderate.\nSouthern, per qt.. 18 25c.\nLettuce\u2014-One California, 2 New York\narrived; 2 reconsigned; 15 cars on track,\nincluding broken. New York express re\nceipts light. Supplies moderate, de\nmand good; market firm. California\nand Washington, crates. Iceberg. 4 to\ndoz.. good quality. $5@5.50. California,\npoor quality, fair condition. $2.50@3, Cow\n$3.60. Ne