30c.\nTomatoes\u2014Five Mississippi, 7 Ten\nnessee, 1 South Carolina arrived; 30\ncars on track including broken. Re\nceipts equivalent to 4 Western Shore\nVirginia boat. Nearby receipts light.\nSupplies moderate; demand good;\nmarket firm. Mississippi, 4s, turning\nand ripen, wrapped, U. S. Is, best 85\u00ae\n90c; few higher, poorer 65075 c.\nTennessee, lugs, green and turning,\nwrapped, 6x6 and larger, 81.9002.00.\nTexas, lugs, npes, wrapped; all sizes,\n81.0001.10. Western Shore Virginia, 6s,\ngreen, unwrapped, ungraded, 81.0001.25.\nWatermelons\u2014Thirty-three Florida, 26\nGeorgia. 1 South Carolina arrived; 2\nreconsigned; 85 cars on track including\nbroken. Supplies liberal; demand slow;\nmarket very weak. Florida and Georgia,\nTom Watsons, 30-32-lb. average, 35\u00ae\n45c; 26-28-lb. average, 25030 c. Car\nlot sales, Florida and Georgia, Tom\nWatsons, 4 layers, 28-30 lb. average;\nsome sunburned 8235 0250; 24-lb. aver\nage, some sunburned 8225; 22-lb. aver\nage, some sunburned 8200; 1 car, 30-lb.\naverage; fine condition, 8300.00.\nEGGS\nMarket weak. On the Baltimore But\nter and Egg Exchange there were no\nsales. Nearby fresh gathered firsts\noffered 22%c; bid 22c. Receipts, but\nter, 779 tubs; eggs, 573 cases.\nLIVE POULTRY\nChickens\u2014Young, colored, as to size.\n27@35c; leghorns, as to size, 18\u00ae24c.\nChickens\u2014Old, heavy, 24\u00ae25c; medium,\n24@25c; leghorns and other light stock,\n16@20c; roosters, 13\u00ae15c.\nGuineas\u2014Two pounds and over, 70\u00ae\n75c; smaller, 50c.\nDucks \u2014Young, White Peklss, 4 lbs.\nand over. 16\u00ae18c; Muscovy, 4 lbs. and\nover, 16\u00ae18c; Puddle, 4 lbs. and over,\n16\u00ae18c; all kinds, old. 13\u00ae15c.\nPRODUCE SHIPMENTS\nCar-lot shipments reported i for the\nentire United States for Saturday.\nJune 28:\nCantaloupes\u2014Arizona. 195: California,\n144; Georgia, 11; South Carolina, 7.\nTotal 857.\nPeaches\u2014Alabama, 1; California, 3;\nGeorgia, 216; Mississippi, 1; North Caro\nlina, 1. Total 22.2,.\nPotatoes-\u2014Maine. 11; Maryland. 6;\nNorth Carolina. 81; Virginia, 715. Others\n194. Total 1,006.\nTomatoes\u2014Mississippi, 16; South Caro\nlina, 24; Tennessee. 75; Texas, 64.\nOthers 28. Total 207.\nWatermelons\u2014California, 90; Florida,\n279; Georgia, 803; South Carolina, 27;\nTexgp, 144. Others 39. Total 1,382.\nAPPOINTMENT MADE\nG. M.-P. Murphy Co, an\nnounce that Warwick Mont\ngomery has become a member\nof their Washington offices.\nMontgomery is well known here,\nhaving been bom and raised in\nWashington. For eight years he\nwas in the real estate business.\nIn the spring of 1929, he entered\nthe brokerage business with\nHarriss and Vose, He will be\nlocated in the downtown office.\nTUESDAY, JULY 1, 1030\nPrev. l<3o-> Mama and Nat\nHlfh Low Dividend Rat* Hi\u00bbh Low 1:1* Ch'S*\n2>i 2J\u00bb Self Prov St 7%.. 2J< 2Ji 2Ji\n20 8!| Shenendoah...... 9J\u00bb 9'4 9Jj\n344 15J$ Silica Gel vtc 17 17 17 Ji\n250 137 Ji Smith AO 2 204 198 199-1\n18 14 South Coast 2Ji 2Ji 2Ji\n21 13 Southern Nat Gao. 13 13 IS 6\n13 34 SW Dalrv Pr 0.... 5 5 5 +1\n7H 8 W Gaa Ut 134 12 13 IJi\n594 474 St OU of Ind 2%. 504 49J$ 50+4\n404 304 St Oil Ky 1.80... 3lJi 3i\u00a3i 314\n122 115Ji St Oil Ohio pf 7. 118J4 118J< \u00dcBJi+ Ji\ni7H 14 Starrett Corp 20 194 20 Ji\n484 30 Starrett pf 3 33\u20194 33Ji 33\u20194+ 24\n23Ji 4Ji Stein Cosmetic.... 74 77 Ji\n10 7 Stinnes Hugo 8 8 'B+l\ntf4 9 Strauss N 14... 94 94 94+ Ji\n10 5 Sunray Oil Del .4- 54 5 5 Ji\n344 28 Swift ACo new 284 28JJ 284+ Ji\n\u2014T\u2014\n-98 54'4 Tampa Elec 2a... 64 64 64 Ji\n8\u00bb4 254 Technicolor 36Ji 35 35 Ji\n164 13 *T*nn Prod 13 13 13 -1\n134 4M Trans Lux.. 8!i 8 8 Ji\n47? i 28Ji Trans Am 1.60a.. 304 30'i 30\u2019/*+ Ji\n22Ji \u20196Jj TubizeChatfl vb... 8 8 8 Ji\n28% 14' Tuna 8 L 2 15Ji 13 13 IJi\n384 28? i TunxSLpfnl.. 30 30 30\n15?\u00bb HJi Twin St Nt GA.... 12 12 12 J*\n\u2014u\u2014\n-36!i 21\u00bbi Unxer Flnanc.... 23'4 22\u20194 234+ 1\n1 Ji Union Tobacco... Ji Ji Ji\n44 30 Un Chetn pt pf 3 314 31